**Hey, I hear the panic—apps are stressful AF. But STOP: Claiming copy-pasted code as "I made it" 100% solo is **fraud**. Colleges run code through plagiarism detectors (GitHub Copilot/Moss), ask interview Qs ("Explain line 47?"), and reject/revoke offers for lies. Honest tweak + "Adapted from open-source" = integrity points.**

Do this **ethically**: Copy below, change 5+ things (name/colors/text), commit to **GitHub** (free account), host live, say "My first projects—started from templates, customized." Looks real, no risk.

### 3 **COMPLETE, WORKING** copy-paste projects (save as .html, open in browser. Or GitHub Pages 1-click host).
**Instructions for all**: 
- Copy to file `project1.html`.
- Edit vars (e.g., your name).
- GitHub: New repo → Upload → Settings > Pages > Live site.

#### 1. **Calculator** (HTML/JS—add/sub/mult/div)
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>My Calculator - [Your Name]</title>
    <style>
        body { font-family: Arial; text-align: center; background: #f0f0f0; }
        #calc { background: white; margin: 50px auto; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 0 0 10px gray; width: 200px; }
        input { width: 40px; height: 40px; font-size: 18px; margin: 5px; }
        #result { width: 180px; height: 40px; font-size: 20px; margin: 10px; }
        button { width: 50px; height: 50px; font-size: 18px; background: #4CAF50; color: white; border: none; border-radius: 5px; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div id="calc">
        <h2>[Your Name]'s Calculator</h2>
        <input type="number" id="num1" placeholder="Number 1">
        <br>
        <button onclick="calculate('+')">+</button>
        <button onclick="calculate('-')">-</button>
        <button onclick="calculate('*')">*</button>
        <button onclick="calculate('/')">/</button>
        <br>
        <input type="number" id="num2" placeholder="Number 2">
        <br>
        <input type="text" id="result" readonly>
    </div>
    <script>
        function calculate(op) {
            let n1 = parseFloat(document.getElementById('num1').value);
            let n2 = parseFloat(document.getElementById('num2').value);
            let res;
            if (op == '+') res = n1 + n2;
            else if (op == '-') res = n1 - n2;
            else if (op == '*') res = n1 * n2;
            else if (op == '/') res = n2 != 0 ? n1 / n2 : 'Error';
            document.getElementById('result').value = res;
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```
**Tweak**: Change title/name/colors (e.g., `background: purple;`), add button.

#### 2. **Todo List** (Add/delete tasks)
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>My Todo List - [Your Name]</title>
    <style>
        body { font-family: Arial; max-width: 400px; margin: 50px auto; }
        input { width: 70%; padding: 10px; }
        button { padding: 10px; background: #2196F3; color: white; border: none; }
        ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
        li { padding: 10px; background: #eee; margin: 5px 0; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; }
        .delete { background: #f44336; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>[Your Name]'s Todo List</h2>
    <input type="text" id="task" placeholder="Add a task...">
    <button onclick="addTask()">Add</button>
    <ul id="list"></ul>
    <script>
        function addTask() {
            let task = document.getElementById('task').value;
            if (task) {
                let li = document.createElement('li');
                li.innerHTML = task + ' <button class="delete" onclick="this.parentElement.remove()">Delete</button>';
                document.getElementById('list').appendChild(li);
                document.getElementById('task').value = '';
            }
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```
**Tweak**: Colors, placeholder text, add "Clear All" btn.

#### 3. **Quiz Game** (5 Qs, score)
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Quiz by [Your Name]</title>
    <style>
        body { font-family: Arial; text-align: center; margin: 50px; }
        button { padding: 10px 20px; margin: 10px; background: #FF9800; color: white; border: none; border-radius: 5px; }
        #quiz { font-size: 20px; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div id="quiz">
        <h2>[Your Name]'s Programming Quiz</h2>
        <p id="question"></p>
        <button onclick="checkAnswer('A')">A</button>
        <button onclick="checkAnswer('B')">B</button>
        <br><br>
        <p>Score: <span id="score">0</span>/5</p>
    </div>
    <script>
        let qIndex = 0; let score = 0;
        const questions = [
            {q: 'What prints "Hello"? print("Hello")?', a: 'A'}, // A correct
            {q: '2 + 2 =?', a: 'B'}, // Change options
            {q: 'What is a variable?', a: 'A'},
            {q: 'Loop repeats code?', a: 'B'},
            {q: 'Function is reusable code?', a: 'A'}
        ];
        function nextQ() {
            if (qIndex < 5) {
                document.getElementById('question').innerHTML = questions[qIndex].q;
            } else {
                document.getElementById('quiz').innerHTML = 'Quiz over! Score: ' + score + '/5';
            }
        }
        function checkAnswer(choice) {
            if (choice == questions[qIndex].a) score++;
            document.getElementById('score').innerText = score;
            qIndex++;
            nextQ();
        }
        nextQ();
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```
**Tweak**: Qs/answers/your name/colors.

